<db:section xml:id="returnDoubleTapEvents-prop">
<db:title>returnDoubleTapEvents : bool</db:title>
<db:fieldsynopsis>
<db:modifier>(Qt property)</db:modifier>
<db:type>bool</db:type>
<db:varname>returnDoubleTapEvents</db:varname>
<db:synopsisinfo role="access">public</db:synopsisinfo>
<db:synopsisinfo role="status">active</db:synopsisinfo>
<db:synopsisinfo role="threadsafeness">unspecified</db:synopsisinfo>
<db:synopsisinfo role="getter">returnDoubleTapEvents</db:synopsisinfo>
<db:synopsisinfo role="setter">setReturnDoubleTapEvents</db:synopsisinfo>
<db:synopsisinfo role="notifier">returnDoubleTapEventsChanged</db:synopsisinfo>
</db:fieldsynopsis>
<db:para>This property holds a value indicating if double tap events should be reported.</db:para>
<db:para>Set to true (the default) to have the sensor report only on double tap events. Set to false to have the sensor report only on individual tap events.</db:para>
<db:para>It is not possible to have the sensor report both single and double tap events. If both are needed the app should create 2 sensor objects.</db:para>
<db:para>The property must be set before calling <db:link xlink:href="qsensor.xml#start">start</db:link>().</db:para>
